	  <h3>1. What is the ROLLER?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>Rolling Potato is the platform where travelers and locals meet up with.No time to plan for your travel? Don't worry.You can make your travel special, in a different way with local friends here.</p>
	  </div>
	  <h3>2. Do I need any certificates to become a Roller?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>Rollers do not require special qualifications.
However, it is a local who wants to meet with curious travelers and make interesting daily trips.
If you love traveling and want to live your life as a travel, be a Roller.</p>
	  </div>
	  <h3>3. How do I register to a Roller?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>On the profile page, click Register Rollers button to go to registration page.
Please verify your mobile phone number which must be contactable.</p>
	  </div>
	  <h3>4.Do Rollers get benefits?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>In Rolling Potato, we organize several seminars related to travel. If you want to be a tourist guide, you will have a related seminar. If you are interested in history, you can have a history seminar. If you want to take pictures better, you can take a photo seminar.
Rollers will benefit from participating in this travel-related seminar organized by Rolling Potato.
We are also planning to benefit for the Rollers when traveling. Plese wait with interest!</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>5.What is the guide?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>This guide is those who have been certified as a tourist guide by a recognized authority in their country.
In Korea, guides are a certified tourist information interpreter.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3> 6.How do I register for a guide?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>On the profile page, click the Register Guide button to go to the guide registration page.
Please verify your mobile phone number which must be contactable.
And, attach photos of your ID and certificate or scanned image. We will review and reply.
We try to get it processed within 3 business days!</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>7. What is the difference between a roller and a guide?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>Rollers are those who love going travel and want to meet new friends.
Rollers do not need special qualifications but the guides requires an official certification.
Rolleres have a limited number of categories for registering travel products, but they can be opened using activity points.
Guides have no limit to the categories in which the travel items can be registered.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>8. How do I register my travel item?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>You can register at profile > Add travel item page.
When registering a travel item, please consider the photos, title, and explanatory texts that express your travel well.
You should also arrange meeting places and tour courses in advance.
Please explain how much it will cost and what it includes or not.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>9. I have a reservation request. What should I do?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>When you receive a reservation request from a traveler, please indicate your acceptance or refusal within 24 hours.
Unless you have to refuse it, please accept it.
If 24 hours have elapsed without an acceptance or rejection statement, the reservation will not be able to proceed because the request has expired.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>10.How can I cancel after the reservation paid?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>After accepting the reservation request, the traveler will make the payment.
After the payment is completed, the reservation will be confirmed. 
Please note that if you cancel from then on, there will be a penalty like the following.
If you cancel first, there is no extra penalty. However, the number of cancellations in the profile is counted so everyone can see it.
If you cancel the second time, the penalty is 100 USD.
If you cancel the third time, the ID will be stopped and you will no longer be able to guide in Rolling Potatoes.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>11. Is there a way to get rid of the cancellation penalty?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>In extenuating circumstances, such as an emergency situation, we can get rid of your cancellation penalty exceptionally.
The extenuating circumstances are follows.
** Serious illness or injury that directly restricts a Roller/guide ability to travel.
** Unexpected death or serious illness of immediate family members (spouse, child, parent, sibling)
** Significant natural disasters or severe weather incidents impacting the location of destination or location of departure
Claims can only be considered after a reservation has been canceled.
Once you've informed your customers(travellers) and canceled a reservation, if you feel that your reason for cancelation is covered by Rolling Potatoâ€™s Extenuating Circumstances Policy, contact Rolling Potato for consideration. We generally require claims to be submitted no later than 14 days from the original travel date and we may require valid supporting documentation.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>12. Do I have to write a review?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>Yes. It is strongly recommended that you write reviews for communicating with travelers.
Every time you write a review, your activity points will be credited.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>13. Do I have to pay a fee?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>Yes. Rolling Potato charges 15% of the transaction commission fee.</p>    
	  </div>
	  <h3>14. How do I get the money?</h3>
	  <div>
	    <p>Please enter your Paypal account on the Profile> Settings page.
After your trip is completed, we will send the amount to your Paypal account, excluding the 15% commission.</p>    
	  </div>
